Actress Tonto Dikeh has revealed why she has not been attending burials. According to her, this is a vow she made while she as a child. The mother one stated this on her Instagram page. The actress also noted that prayer is what her family needs from friends and not condolences messages or money as she would prefer to grieve privately. The Nollywood star recently lost her stepmother, taking her away from social media for a while.   Adekunle Gold promises a song for Man Utd if…     Why I don’t attend burial ceremonies, by Tonto Dikeh     Peruzzi to headline Carica pre-launch   - Advertisement - “I have never attended a burial before. I will never attend one too. I said this when I was a child and I stick by it “My mum’s burial will/might be my first ever. To all my friends who think I am shutting them out, my reason is I don’t attend burials. “If I let you attend my mum’s I will owe you the same favour and I can’t repay that. If you love me, pray for my family. If you intend to support me, only pray for me. “Don’t send a dime or a consolation message. I don’t do so well with that! But know I appreciate you all a lot and I’m grateful.” “My pain is bigger than you think. Your presence may mean a lot but I’ll love to grieve privately,” she wrote.